                    "id": "horizontal_diffusivity_unstable",
                    "description": "Horizontal eddy diffusivity K_yy under unstable conditions (Eq. 18.128): K_yy = 0.1*w_star*z_i, independent of height. At z = 200 m, L_MO = -100 m K_yy = 87.72 m^2/s while the vertical diffusivity K_zz (Eq. 18.121 piece 2, z/z_i = 0.2) is larger — the test pins both, reproducing the unstable assertion of the upstream `Horizontal Diffusivity K_yy` testitem.",
                    "parameter_overrides": {
