                    "description": "Power-law wind profile (Eq. 18.118): mean wind speed u_wind = u_r*(z/z_r)^p_wind swept over height z from 10 to 1500 m at the default parameters. Reproduces the classic logarithmic-looking wind profile that anchors the docs `Wind Speed Profile` figure — wind speed rising monotonically with height, passing through the reference point (u_r, z_r) = (5 m/s, 10 m).",
