                    "id": "unstable_eddy_diffusivity_profile",
                    "description": "Vertical and horizontal eddy diffusivity profiles under unstable (convective) conditions (L_MO = -100 m), swept over height z from 10 to 1500 m. K_zz follows the four-piece Eq. 18.121 profile of Lamb & Duran (1977) — rising through the surface and mixed layers, peaking near z/z_i ~ 0.3, then decaying toward the residual constant above the boundary layer — while K_yy = 0.1*w_star*z_i (Eq. 18.128) stays constant with height. Reproduces the docs `Vertical Eddy Diffusivity Profiles` and `Horizontal vs Vertical Diffusivity` figures for the unstable case.",
